      "text": " **Remark 1.** If  $H$  is infinite-dimensional and  $f$  is a bijective transformation of  $\\mathcal{G}^{k}(H)$  preserving the ortho-adjacency in both directions, then  $X \\to f(X^{\\perp})^{\\perp}$  is a bijective transformation of  $\\mathcal{G}_{k}(H)$  which also preserves the ortho-adjacency in both directions. If the latter transformation is induced by a unitary or anti-unitary operator  $U$ , then  $f$  is also induced by  $U$ .",
